cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL 

This paper is about adapting deep neural networks to changing environments for semantic segmentation. The primary focus is on computer vision (CV) tasks, specifically semantic segmentation, which suggests that cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The use of memory to prevent catastrophic forgetting is a common technique in reinforcement learning (RL) and robotics (RO), making cs.RO a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of stylized data, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer linguistics (CL), making cs.CL a possible sub-category.
